AdditionalDetails.Name: webdescriptionshort
AdditionalDetails.Value: Coconut and Pineapple Flavour Sparkling Mixed Drink with Caribbean Rum. A delightful blend of Caribbean rum and sparkling fresh pineapple. Well-balanced and tropical, with a slight sweetness and the distinctive character of Malibu Caribbean rum. Malibu Rum & Pineapple cans are ideal for any occasion, whether you're having a summer BBQ at home, partying at a festival, or having a picnic in the park.We've combined our classic Malibu Coconut flavoured rum with refreshing sparkling pineapple to create these cans, perfect when the sun's setting and the good times are flowing. Recreate those holiday feels all year round and introduce a bit of sunshine to your drink! Malibu's story goes back to 1982 when the creators were looking for a way to simplify the Pina Colada. The Caribbean rum base is produced at the West Indies Rum Distillery, a world renowned distillery founded in 1893. Every drop is filled with sun, music, beaches, parties, new friends, love, and adventures. Malibu is the world's favourite Coconut Rum, so it's no surprise that you'll find it in bars worldwide. As much Malibu loves the Pina Colada, there's so much more you can make with Malibu Coconut, and their other flavours and cans. Check out the Malibu Instagram @malibu_rum or website to get some cocktail inspiration and take your hosting game to the next level!

AdditionalDetails.Name: product_short_name
AdditionalDetails.Value: Echuca Distillery Long Island Iced Tea Cocktail Spirit

AdditionalDetails.Name: webdescriptionshort
AdditionalDetails.Value:
A combination of Echuca Distillerys High St Dry Gin, Gold Agave Spirit, Coconut Flower Spirit, Lemon Myrtle Vodka & Orange Liqueur. 100% handcrafted, produced and distilled in Echuca.
Makes a great Long Island Iced Tea:
  • 60ml Echuca Distillery Long Island Iced Tea Cocktail Spirit
  • 15ml Lime Juice
  • 60ml Cola (we prefer coke but any cola will do)
  • Ice
  • Lime Wedge for garnish.
Method:
  1. Fill Cocktail Shaker with ice.
  2. Add spirit & lime juice into Shaker & shake vigorously until frothy.
  3. Fill a Highball Glass with ice.
  4. Add cola.
  5. Strain contents of Shaker on top.
  6. Garnish with Lime. (wedge or wheel)
You will need to supply:
  • Cocktail Shaker
  • Ice Cubes
  • Cola
  • Lime Juice
  • Lime for Garnish

Products.RichDescription: Kizakura Yuzu Highball is new series of Japanese R.T.D (ready to drink) Sake Cocktail. Yuzu is a kind of Japanese citrus cross between lemon, lime & orange. Espresso Martini 6-Pack
Experience the allure of our specially curated 6-Pack of Espresso Martini cocktails, a blend that effortlessly marries the robust depth of freshly brewed espresso with the smooth elegance of premium vodka. Hints of coffee liqueur elevate the richness, ensuring each sip carries a velvety texture and a sumptuous finish. Every meticulously crafted cocktail is encased in a chic glass bottle, reflecting the luxe essence of its contents.
Nestled within a sophisticated black display box adorned with an embossed stamp, the packaging exudes a timeless elegance. For those who appreciate the finer things, this collection melds flavor sophistication with aesthetic brilliance, making it an unmissable addition to any cocktail connoisseur's collection.
Espresso Martini History
What do the Sex Pistols, Margaret Thatcher and the Espresso Martini have in common?Well, we dont know if all three were ever in the same bar at the same time, but we do know they all found fame (and some say notoriety) in 1980s London.
There are several claims for the origin of the Espresso Martini. The more common claim was created at Freds Club, a Soho bar in the late 80s by bartender Dick Bradsell, for a young model who wanted something to wake me up and f**k me up. We cant think of a drink that better embodies the spirit of London. With many variations, this perfect recipe combines Vodka, Cold Brew Coffee Liquor, Espresso Coffee Extract, and sugar cane. Its an ideal cocktail for those who need an extra shot of life to make it through the night.
Serving Suggestions
To serve, fill a cocktail shaker with ice, pour Dr Onyx Espresso Martini and shake vigorously. Strain into a chilled martini glass and garnish with fresh coffee beans.
Ingredients
Vodka, Coffee Liqueur, Coffee Espresso, Sugar Cane Syrup, Water.
Volume
100ml, 16% Alcohol, Approx. 1.3 Standard Drinks.100ml, 16% Alcohol, Approx. 1.3 Standard Drinks.

Old Fashioned 6-Pack
Experience the timeless allure of our 6-Pack of Old Fashioned cocktails, meticulously crafted to honor a classic. Every bottle reveals a captivating symphony of robust whiskey, a hint of sugar, and the aromatic embrace of bitters, crowned with a citrus twist. This blend results in a cocktail that's both bold in flavor and smooth in finish, capturing the very essence of a bygone era.
The drink's rich, amber elegance is accentuated within a beautifully contoured glass bottle, encapsulating its majesty. All are housed in a sophisticated classic black box, adorned with an embossed stamp, underscoring the premium essence of this collection. For the true connoisseur, our Old Fashioned set represents a harmonious fusion of taste, tradition, and artistry.
Old Fashioned History
The Old Fashioned is said to have been first created at the Pendennis Club, a famous gentlemen's club in Louisville, Kentucky in 1881 in honour of Colonel James E. Pepper famed bourbon distiller, who then introduced it to New York high society during his frequent visits to the Waldorf-Astoria Hotel bar in New York. They clearly embraced it, given how the infamous Mad Men had such a taste for it 80 years later in the 1960s Manhattan advertising scene. The Old Fashioned has had a makeover or two over its time. But this smooth, bitter, sweet simplicity of Straight Bourbon Whiskey, traditional Bitters, and sugar cane syrup is a tonic that Don Draper himself would approve of.
Serving Suggestions
Serve Dr Onyx Old Fashioned gently swirled in a short glass over ice, with a twist of orange zest. Pinch the zest so the oils spray over the drink before dropping it into the glass.
Ingredients
Bourbon Whiskey, Sugar Cane Syrup, Bitters, Water.
Volume
100ml, 30% Alcohol, Approx. 2.4 Standard Drinks.

Manhattan:
The first skyscrapers began to change the skyline of Manhattan Island in the 1880s, just as NYCs Manhattan Club claims they created the first Manhattan cocktail.  And its making just as big an impact 140 or so years later, capturing all the glamour and excitement of New York City in a glass. The Manhattan has stayed true to its origins, mixing American Rye Whiskey, Sweet Vermouth, and traditional Angostura Bitters. During Prohibition (19201933) Canadian whisky was primarily used because it was more readily available.  Just like its namesake, and the people who call it home, it has survived wars and prohibition, recessions and depressions. 
Serving Suggestions:
To serve, pour Dr Onyx Manhattan into a mixing glass filled with ice, stir well, then strain into a chilled cocktail glass or in a short glass over ice. Garnish with a cherry or lemon peel.

There are many claims to the origin of the Margarita.  Some say it evolved from the traditional Tequila Daisy (Margarita is Spanish for Daisy), similar to the Margarita with more focus on lemon and lime, than the balance of orange liquor in the Margarita. Others say it was created in a Tijuana bar for the Ziegfeld dancer Majorie King. Another popular story is that it was created by socialite Margarita Sames for guests at her Acapulco holiday home.

Margarita:
There are many claims to the origin of the Margarita.  Some say it evolved from the traditional Tequila Daisy (Margarita is Spanish for Daisy), similar to the Margarita with more focus on lemon and lime, than the balance of orange liquor in the Margarita. Others say it was created in a Tijuana bar for the Ziegfeld dancer Majorie King. Another popular story is that it was created by socialite Margarita Sames for guests at her Acapulco holiday home.  Regardless of how it originated, the blend of Tequila, Cointreau Liqueur, and lime is one of the most popular cocktails of choice.
Serving Suggestions:
To serve, line the rim of a tumbler with fresh lime and dip the rim in salt.  Fill the glass with ice, then pour Dr Onyx Margarita.  Add a squeeze of fresh lime and drop in a lime wedge to complete your south of the border experience.

Tequila, Orange Liqueur, Lime Juice Cordial, Water.

100ml, 27% Alcohol, Approx. 2.1 Standard Drinks.

Speakeasy 500ml Dry Martini
Step into an era of sophistication with our 'Speakeasy' Dry Martini. This 500ml hand-crafted gem offers a harmonious blend of premium gin and dry vermouth, balanced to perfection, evoking the elegance of the Roaring Twenties. Each sip reveals subtle botanical undertones, elevated by a hint of citrus, culminating in a crisp, refined finish.
Encased in a gracefully contoured glass bottle, the martini's clarity and shimmer shine through, paying homage to its storied history. The luxurious packaging, with its classic black theme and embossed details, adds a touch of opulence, making this Dry Martini not only a delightful drink but a visual feast.
Dry Martini History
Ernest Hemingway described the Martini best Ive never tasted anything so cool and clean...They make me feel civilised. It was James Bonds drink of choice where the catchphrase "shaken, not stirred" was introduced in Diamonds Are Forever (1956), and then incorrectly referred to as "stirred, not shaken" in You Only Live Twice (1967), to Bond's response "Perfect".
The Martini rose to prominence during the 1950s and 60s when the three-martini lunch was widespread. Whilst the stance on workplace drinking might have changed, our affection for the Martini hasnt. An excellent tonic for those wanting to step back to a more sophisticated time.
Serving Suggestions
To serve, pour Dr Onyx Dry Martini into a mixing glass filled with ice. Stir, and strain into a chilled martini glass. Garnish with an olive or citrus zest, squeeze to release the oils over the glass before you dropping it in.
Ingredients
Dry Gin, Dry Vermouth, Bitters, Water.
Volume
500ml, 30% Alcohol, Approx. 12 Standard Drinks.

Speakeasy 500ml Espresso Martini
Experience the allure of the Roaring Twenties with our Speakeasy Espresso Martini. Crafted with precision, this 500ml elixir intertwines the rich, aromatic notes of freshly brewed coffee with the velvety texture of premium vodka, hinting at dark chocolate and subtle vanilla nuances. Every sip is a rendezvous of intense flavors, awakening the senses.
The cocktails deep allure is further magnified by its elegantly designed glass bottle, capturing the essence of the Jazz Age in every reflection. Presented in a sophisticated classic black box, adorned with embossed stamping, this Espresso Martini promises a drink thats as aesthetically pleasing as it is delectably satisfying.
Espresso Martini History
What do the Sex Pistols, Margaret Thatcher and the Espresso Martini have in common?Well, we dont know if all three were ever in the same bar at the same time, but we do know they all found fame (and some say notoriety) in 1980s London. There are several claims for the origin of the Espresso Martini.
The more common claim was created at Freds Club, a Soho bar in the late 80s by bartender Dick Bradsell, for a young model who wanted something to wake me up and f**k me up. We cant think of a drink that better embodies the spirit of London. With many variations, this perfect recipe combines Vodka, Cold Brew Coffee Liquor, Espresso Coffee Extract, and sugar cane. Its an ideal cocktail for those who need an extra shot of life to make it through the night.
Serving Suggestions
To serve, fill a cocktail shaker with ice, pour Dr Onyx Espresso Martini and shake vigorously. Strain into a chilled martini glass and garnish with fresh coffee beans.
Ingredients
Vodka, Coffee Liqueur, Coffee Espresso, Sugar Cane Syrup, Water.
Volume
500ml, 16% Alcohol, Approx. 7.0 Standard Drinks.

Wax Platinum Margarita Gift Set
Step into the realm of luxury with our 'Wax Platinum Gift Set', an epitome of finesse and artful craftsmanship. Central to this curated ensemble is a hand-crafted Margarita, concocted with precision to exude the vibrant zest and essence that Margarita enthusiasts cherish.
The bottle, an art piece in its own right, has been delicately hand-dipped in wax, ensuring its exclusivity. It is then lovingly nestled within an ornate, hand-wax dripped canister case, elevating its aesthetic allure. With our unwavering dedication to high-end spirits, every facet of this gift set promises an experience in grandeur and refinement, making it an impeccable choice for discerning aficionados.
Margarita History
There are many claims to the origin of the Margarita.Some say it evolved from the traditional Tequila Daisy (Margarita is Spanish for Daisy), similar to the Margarita with more focus on lemon and lime, than the balance of orange liquor in the Margarita.
Others say it was created in a Tijuana bar for the Ziegfeld dancer Majorie King. Another popular story is that it was created by socialite Margarita Sames for guests at her Acapulco holiday home.Regardless of how it originated, the blend of Tequila, Cointreau Liqueur, and lime is one of the most popular cocktails of choice.
Serving Suggestions
To serve, line the rim of a tumbler with fresh lime and dip the rim in salt.Fill the glass with ice, then pour Dr Onyx Margarita.Add a squeeze of fresh lime and drop in a lime wedge to complete your south of the border experience.
Ingredients
Tequila, Orange Liqueur, Lime Syrup, Water.
Volume
500mL, 27% Alcohol, Approx. 10 Standard Drinks.

Speakeasy 500ml Negroni
Transport your senses to the glamorous era of the 1920s with our Speakeasy Negroni cocktail. Expertly mixed in a 500ml measure, this hand-crafted concoction artfully balances the bitterness of premium gin with the sweet vermouth and the complex, herbaceous notes of Campari. This harmonious blend offers a taste that is both robust and refreshing, echoing the vivacity of the times it celebrates.
Encased in a meticulously designed glass bottle that radiates sophistication, the ruby-red hue of the cocktail invites admiration. The presentation reaches its pinnacle with a high-end, classic black box, etched with intricate embossing, solidifying the 'Speakeasy' Negroni's position as a drink of timeless elegance.
Negroni History
There are many stories about who created the first Negroni. We like to believe it originated in Florence, Italy in 1919 when Count Camillo Negroni asked for a stronger version of his favourite cocktail the Americano (Campari, Red Vermouth and soda water). The bartender replaced the traditional soda for gin, and the world-famous aperitif was born.
The definition of sophistication and simplicity the Negroni is a tonic for those who would rather be sitting in a local bar during what the Italians refer to as aperitivo hour.
Serving Suggestions
Serve Dr Onyx Negroni swirled, not shaken in a short glass over ice. Traditionally garnished with a slice of orange or the preferred blood orange adding a more dramatic fragrance, and a sweet and tart flavour.
Ingredients
Dry Gin, Campari, Vermouth, Orange Bitters, Water.
Volume
500ml, 22% Alcohol, Approx. 9.0 Standard Drinks.

Samai Distillery started back in 2014, using the highest quality molasses from local sugar cane to produce their rums along with drops of Cambodian honey. A combination of pot and column distillation is used, the pot still giving a rich spirit full of character and the column providing a light rum to blend.




The rums are aged in a combination of French oak, American Bourbon barrels and Spanish sherry casks to create a seamless blend of mature flavours.
Nose: Sweet notes of vanilla, molasses and honey.
Palate: Hints of oak, vanilla and honey are married together and a slight persisting sweetness.
Overall: A great everyday drinking rum for those who like those classic rum flavours with a Cambodian twist.

About Xicaru Mezcal: Xicaru, the Zapotec word for beautiful, reflects Fernando Santibanez's desire to share a traditionally produced mezcal that is approachable and distinct. Using his grandmothers recipe, Fernando makes small batches of Xicaru Mezcal with time-honoured methods at a Palenque in Matatlan, Oaxaca. This mezcal showcases the 100% Agave espadin from which its made. Its natural smoky flavour is derived by cooking the agave in a conical stone oven on mesquite and ocote, woods native to Oaxaca.
